# Structure Update Guidelines

This file records user-provided notes for upcoming structure changes.

Use it as a working handoff document for agents that will implement those
changes later. Add only changes and constraints explicitly provided by the user.

When adding new notes, place them where they make the file easiest to understand,
not automatically at the bottom. The file may be rewritten as the structure
discussion evolves.

## Hard Earned Lessons

- Use "submission" for the artificial Lean Meta Library entry. Do not call this
  a repo. Use "repository" only when referring to the actual source-code
  repository or GitHub repository URL.
- A submission can contain two Lake packages: a statement-package and a
  proof-package.
- Statement-package and proof-package are Lake packages inside a submission, not
  submissions themselves.

## Package Structure

- Submissions no longer need separate proof and surface packages.
- Remove tests that require or enforce the old separate proof-package and
  surface-package structure.
- A proof package depending locally on `Slug.Surface` from `./surface-package`
  is no longer expected, but it remains allowed.
- Do not require a unique Lean library for each statement folder. Each statement
  must still be included in the shared Surface/Statement library.
- Rename the "surface" concept to "statements" throughout the new structure:
  the surface package becomes the statement package, surface files become
  statement files, and related surface terminology should become statement
  terminology.
- Do not add this point prominently to the README, because presenting the old
  proof/surface package distinction there would be confusing.

## Statement Declarations

- Surface/Statement entries must only allow axioms. They should no longer allow
  theorems.

